Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->add( t=>'Real', A=>'Real', B=>'Real', C=>'Real' );
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$r1 = random(2,5,1);
$r2 = $r1 + 1;
$r1pr2 = $r1+$r2;
$r1tr2 = $r1*$r2;

TEXT(beginproblem());
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Solve the initial value problem.
\( y''+ $r1pr2 y'+ $r1tr2 y=0, \qquad y(0)=1, y'(0)=0. \)

$PAR
\(y(t) = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( Compute("-$r1*e^(-$r2*t) + $r2*e^(-$r1*t)")->cmp() );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

The characteristic equation is
\[ r^2 + $r1pr2 r + $r1tr2 = 0, \]
which has the solutions \(r=-$r1\) and \(r=-$r2\), so that
\[ y(t) = A e^{-$r2 t} + B e^{-$r1 t}. \]

The initial condition \(y(0)=1\) gives
\[ A+B=1 \]
and
\(y'(0)=0\) gives
\[ -$r2 A - $r1 B=0\]
so that
\( A= -$r1\) and \(B= $r2\)
and
\[ y(t) = -$r1 e^{-$r2 t} + $r2 e^{-$r1 t}. \]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();
